@prefix ex: <https://vocab.cfaa.eus/broaching/> .
ex:ToolInspection ex:textoExtracto """Begin tool inspection. Tool inspection may be accessed from the vertical softkey menu only when the execution of the program has been interrupted ([STOP] key). After activating tool inspection, it is possible to jog the axes using the jog keyboard, act upon the master spindle of the channel from the operator panel and execute blocks from the MDI/MDA mode. Execute blocks in MDI/MDA mode. Any program block may be executed in MDI/MDA mode. The conditions when entering the MDI/MDA mode will be those of the interruption point; i.e. the CNC maintains the history of active G and M functions, feedrate, spindle speed, tool and other commands that were programmed. However, the CNC treats certain functions and commands (type of movements, radius compensation, etc.) differently. Refer to the operating manual. In general, all the changes made in MDI/MDA mode are kept active when resuming the program after tool inspection except the following functions that are restored at the time of interruption; type of interpolation (G00, G01, G02, G03, G33 or G63), G90/G91 function or #MCS function. Repositioning the axes and the spindle. To complete the tool inspection and before resuming the execution of the program, the spindle turning direction must be restored and the axes repositioned.""" ;
    a ex:TareaMantenimiento ;
    ex:textoExtracto """Tool inspection may be accessed from the vertical softkey menu only when the execution of the program has been interrupted ([STOP] key).""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """After activating tool inspection, it is possible to jog the axes using the jog keyboard, act upon the master spindle of the channel from the operator panel and execute blocks from the MDI/MDA mode.""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """Execute blocks in MDI/MDA mode. Any program block may be executed in MDI/MDA mode.""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """The conditions when entering the MDI/MDA mode will be those of the interruption point; i.e. the CNC maintains the history of active G and M functions, feedrate, spindle speed, tool and other commands that were programmed.""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """However, the CNC treats certain functions and commands (type of movements, radius compensation, etc.) differently.""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """In general, all the changes made in MDI/MDA mode are kept active when resuming the program after tool inspection except the following functions that are restored at the time of interruption; type of interpolation (G00, G01, G02, G03, G33 or G63), G90/G91 function or #MCS function.""" ;
    ex:textoExtracto """Repositioning the axes and the spindle. To complete the tool inspection and before resuming the execution of the program, the spindle turning direction must be restored and the axes repositioned.""" .

ex:MDI_MDA_Mode ex:textoExtracto """execute blocks from the MDI/MDA mode""" ;
    a ex:ModoOperacion ;
    ex:textoExtracto """MDI/MDA mode""" .

ex:JogKeyboard ex:textoExtracto """jog the axes using the jog keyboard""" ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:textoExtracto """jog keyboard""" .

ex:OperatorPanel ex:textoExtracto """act upon the master spindle of the channel from the operator panel""" ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:textoExtracto """operator panel""" .

ex:StopKey ex:textoExtracto """the execution of the program has been interrupted ([STOP] key)""" ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:textoExtracto """[STOP] key""" .

ex:VerticalSoftkeyMenu ex:textoExtracto """accessed from the vertical softkey menu""" ;
    a ex:InterfazUsuario ;
    ex:textoExtracto """vertical softkey menu""" .